WEBVTT

00:01.935 --> 00:03.903
<i>Connor ran off
with all the money.</i>

00:03.969 --> 00:07.303
As of noon today, all of the Meade
accounts have been totally cleared out.

00:07.340 --> 00:08.534
We clean up our own mess.

00:08.575 --> 00:10.736
I'm gonna start liquidating
my personal assets.

00:10.777 --> 00:11.835
Everything I've got.

00:11.878 --> 00:13.539
I'll contribute as much as I can.

00:13.580 --> 00:15.741
<i>Which fabulous fashion world editor</i>

00:15.782 --> 00:18.478
<i>has begun to sell off her clothes
Willie-nilly?</i>

00:20.120 --> 00:22.588
<i>I have a son now,
and it's his company, too.</i>

00:22.622 --> 00:26.888
Have to be careful, though, sometimes,
remind myself that I am not his mother.

00:26.927 --> 00:28.485
<i>But a bus,
really, Daniel?</i>

00:28.528 --> 00:30.155
This is the lowest moment of my life.

00:30.197 --> 00:31.994
For God's sake, hold on to the pole!

00:32.031 --> 00:33.727
No way,
I don't know who touched that thing.

00:33.800 --> 00:36.234
My family is sort of really wealthy.

00:36.269 --> 00:38.396
<i>I just feel like
I don't know that much about you.</i>

00:38.472 --> 00:40.838
<i>Well, here's something else
you might not know.</i>

00:40.874 --> 00:42.637
<i>I'm kind of really into you.</i>

00:48.482 --> 00:52.475
<i>Bounce, bounce, bounce
Bounce, bounce</i>

00:52.519 --> 00:54.510
<i>Build it up</i>

00:55.622 --> 00:57.351
<i>Tear it down</i>

00:58.859 --> 01:00.759
<i>Build it up</i>

01:02.028 --> 01:03.893
<i>Tear it down</i>

01:05.000 --> 01:11.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:16.910 --> 01:22.177
<i>Bounce, bounce, bounce
Bounce, bounce</i>

01:24.217 --> 01:25.684
Thank you.

01:28.555 --> 01:31.786
For the record, I've decided
the limo treatment doesn't suck.

01:31.825 --> 01:34.988
Noted. Also for the record,
I'm not really a limo kind of guy.

01:35.028 --> 01:38.464
I just thought it might be fun,
since it's, you know, Tuesday.

01:38.498 --> 01:41.331
Tuesday.
Now officially known as Limo Day.

01:41.401 --> 01:44.097
But seriously, Matt, stop pampering me.
It makes me feel guilty.

01:44.171 --> 01:46.230
Damn. There goes
Hot Air Balloon Wednesday.

01:47.407 --> 01:50.535
Sounds good, doesn't it?
Seriously, I can make that happen.

01:50.577 --> 01:52.636
I know. I believe you, but it just...

01:52.679 --> 01:57.139
It all feels like a little much, you know,
with the cutbacks at work, and...

01:57.184 --> 02:00.551
I know, I know, but for you,
Hot Air Balloon Wednesday,

02:00.587 --> 02:02.487
Submarine Thursday...

02:02.522 --> 02:05.980
As long as it makes you happy,
just name it. Anything.

02:06.026 --> 02:08.460
Well, I don't think you could make me
any more happy,

02:08.495 --> 02:09.519
but I'm gonna go out on a limb

02:09.562 --> 02:11.394
and say that things at work
are gonna get better.

02:11.431 --> 02:12.659
- Really?
- Yeah.

02:12.699 --> 02:15.190
It's sort of my grand unified theory
of happiness.

02:15.268 --> 02:17.259
With us so good,
how could work be bad?

02:22.375 --> 02:23.399
Coming through.

02:23.476 --> 02:25.910
Excuse me, sorry, just trying to get out.

02:25.946 --> 02:27.243
Hey, watch it.

02:30.684 --> 02:32.208
- Excuse me. Sorry.
- What is going on?

02:32.252 --> 02:34.015
Hey! That's mine.

02:35.522 --> 02:38.616
<i>Mode magazine, please hold.
Mode magazine, hold.</i>

02:38.658 --> 02:40.751
No, he's not available. Please hold.

02:40.794 --> 02:42.227
- Amanda.
- Hey!

02:42.262 --> 02:44.924
<i>You cannot just take that.
That is Mode property.</i>

02:44.965 --> 02:47.058
Breathe, Mandy, breathe.

02:48.235 --> 02:49.395
Guys, what is going on?

02:49.469 --> 02:53.098
We're being looted. I feel so violated.
And not in a good way.

02:53.173 --> 02:55.641
Didn't you hear?
The "Sex" issue was a limp noodle,

02:55.709 --> 02:57.870
and now they've cut the budget
to the bone.

02:57.911 --> 02:59.071
God, this is so depressing.

02:59.112 --> 03:02.639
I just used the word "noodle"
and "bone," and I got nothing.

03:02.682 --> 03:06.413
Apparently, everything leased or
considered non-essential has to go.

03:06.453 --> 03:08.751
I'm looking for Betty Suarez.

03:10.123 --> 03:13.354
Do you need any help
loading her onto the truck?

03:14.060 --> 03:17.860
- You need my ID for a delivery?
- It's protocol.

03:24.104 --> 03:25.503
Sign here.

03:27.974 --> 03:29.236
And here.

03:29.276 --> 03:30.903
Is this all really necessary?

03:30.944 --> 03:34.345
Initial here. And I need your thumbprint.

03:34.848 --> 03:36.315
My thumbprint?

03:37.417 --> 03:38.543
<i>Identity confirmed.</i>

03:38.585 --> 03:39.609
Whoa!

03:39.653 --> 03:41.518
The Calvin Hartley
Charitable Foundation requires

03:41.554 --> 03:43.317
positive identification of all recipients.

03:43.356 --> 03:45.256
The Hartley Charitable Foundation?

03:45.292 --> 03:48.523
Did he say the Hartley
Charitable Foundation?

03:48.561 --> 03:51.394
Daniel, what's going on?
They're repossessing everything.

03:51.431 --> 03:54.992
Betty... Please, with
everything falling apart around here,

03:55.068 --> 03:57.536
just let me have this moment.

04:00.373 --> 04:03.604
Every year, Cal Hartley hosts
a charity Easter egg hunt

04:03.643 --> 04:05.440
at the Museum of Natural History.

04:05.478 --> 04:08.606
- Wait. Cal Hartley?
- It's incredibly exclusive.

04:10.050 --> 04:13.178
I've been trying to score an invite
for years.

04:13.420 --> 04:16.149
Daniel, I think maybe this might be...

04:16.856 --> 04:19.290
"The Calvin Hartley
Charitable Foundation

04:19.326 --> 04:23.057
"is pleased to invite Betty Suarez"?

04:24.464 --> 04:27.228
Cal Hartley is Matt's father.

04:28.535 --> 04:33.165
Of course. Matt Hartley. I don't know
why I never put that together.

04:33.239 --> 04:37.369
So, things are going really great
with you and Matt, I guess.

04:37.410 --> 04:41.141
- Yeah.
- Seeing as you got the big egg-vite.

04:43.383 --> 04:45.283
Here you are.

04:45.318 --> 04:48.219
Sorry, Daniel. I had no idea.

04:48.254 --> 04:51.519
No, no, it's fine. I'm sure you're gonna
have fun mingling with the billionaires

04:51.558 --> 04:55.255
and the princesses
and the popes and the...

04:55.295 --> 04:58.264
Sorry, Daniel, one second. Hello.

04:58.298 --> 05:00.425
Aunt Betty, don't ever break up
with Matt.

05:00.467 --> 05:02.958
- Why do you need my fingerprints?
- What are you talking about?

05:03.036 --> 05:05.561
<i>We just got an invitation to
the Hartley Easter egg hunt.</i>

05:05.638 --> 05:07.105
<i>Do you know how exclusive this is?</i>

05:07.173 --> 05:09.266
<i>I'm a US citizen.
- I have an idea.</i>

05:09.309 --> 05:13.245
- I have rights, you know.
- Grandpa, give him the thumbprint.

05:13.279 --> 05:15.645
You're not going
to mess this up for me.

05:17.183 --> 05:18.377
Go.

05:18.418 --> 05:20.511
Look, Justin, I don't really
have time for this right now,

05:20.553 --> 05:22.020
but I'll call you back, okay? Bye.

05:26.693 --> 05:27.751
Everything okay?

05:27.794 --> 05:32.356
Yeah, he was just really excited
about going to the Hartley thing.

05:34.367 --> 05:36.858
Your family got an egg-vitation?

05:56.689 --> 05:59.988
That is beautiful, Willie.
You are one magnificent mama.

06:00.060 --> 06:04.463
Thank you, Miles.
Can we take a break, please?

06:05.165 --> 06:08.532
Christina. Come get him.

06:09.969 --> 06:11.402
Come on, little man.

06:11.438 --> 06:13.906
My back is killing me.

06:13.940 --> 06:18.309
You poor thing. You've been holding
him for, what? A whole five minutes.

06:18.344 --> 06:20.403
Try doing it for nine months.

06:20.447 --> 06:24.349
Yes, yes, yes, you're a saint.
And his diaper's full, as well.

06:25.318 --> 06:29.186
Miles, darling, thank you so much
for capturing these precious moments.

06:29.222 --> 06:32.885
It's my pleasure, Wilhelmina.
That woman...

06:32.926 --> 06:34.553
She's my surrogate.

06:34.594 --> 06:37.961
She's helping me out until I find
a more suitable nanny arrangement.

06:37.997 --> 06:39.794
Was she your egg donor as well?

06:39.833 --> 06:43.793
What? No.
Why would you suggest such a thing?

06:43.871 --> 06:46.203
Well, the baby doesn't
exactly look like you.

06:46.240 --> 06:48.765
But, Miles, his father's white.
What do you expect?

06:48.843 --> 06:50.367
I mean, he'll brown up eventually.

06:50.444 --> 06:51.775
No, it's not just that, Wilhelmina.

06:51.812 --> 06:54.246
My business is seeing,
especially faces,

06:54.281 --> 06:57.341
and your child really looks
like that woman.

06:57.384 --> 06:59.944
Well, that's preposterous.

07:04.592 --> 07:07.152
Listen, not to worry,
I can work wonders with Photoshop.

07:07.194 --> 07:08.855
I'll give him the Slater chin.

07:21.742 --> 07:23.642
<i>From the summit
of Mount Everest</i>

07:23.677 --> 07:25.611
<i>to the heights of Earth's orbit,</i>

07:25.646 --> 07:28.206
<i>whether he's brokering peace
in the Middle East,</i>

07:28.249 --> 07:33.516
<i>inventing a new artificial hip,
or winning his third Indianapolis 500,</i>

07:33.554 --> 07:37.854
<i>Cal Hartley personifies
the pinnacle of human achievement.</i>

07:37.892 --> 07:41.259
<i>Billionaire, philanthropist, innovator.</i>

07:41.295 --> 07:45.197
<i>There is no part of your life
that Cal Hartley hasn't touched</i>

07:45.232 --> 07:47.427
<i>and probably made better.</i>

07:49.069 --> 07:50.934
- Wow.
- Yep, that's Dad.

07:50.971 --> 07:52.131
Please adopt me.

07:52.206 --> 07:54.606
Forget it, unless you take me, too.

07:54.642 --> 07:58.339
Matt, we really appreciate you
inviting us to your father's fundraiser,

07:58.379 --> 08:01.712
but I just feel we wouldn't fit in.

08:01.749 --> 08:04.809
Don't even go there, Grandpa.
I've been waiting for this my whole life.

08:04.852 --> 08:06.843
Yeah, and I hear that they have a real

08:06.887 --> 08:07.979
Faberge egg

08:08.022 --> 08:11.287
hidden in with the Easter eggs.
I'm so finding it.

08:11.325 --> 08:12.690
Fabergé.

08:12.993 --> 08:16.827
No, sweetie, when
there's an "E" at the end, it's silent.

08:16.864 --> 08:19.230
Matt, are you sure you want to do this?

08:19.266 --> 08:22.167
I mean, I didn't exactly start off
on the right foot with your mom,

08:22.236 --> 08:24.170
and I was hoping for less pressure
with your dad.

08:24.205 --> 08:26.173
You know, maybe we could
have him over for dinner.

08:26.240 --> 08:30.040
<i>Papi could cook, and we'll just talk
about mountain climbing.</i>

08:30.077 --> 08:33.376
Well, you know,
meeting my father is a really big deal.

08:33.414 --> 08:36.212
I mean, this guy turns down
invitations to the White House.

08:36.250 --> 08:37.774
Matt, you're not helping.

08:37.818 --> 08:42.881
Look, the point is, four
former presidents want to meet that guy.

08:42.923 --> 08:46.552
But to me, "that guy" is Dad.

08:48.629 --> 08:51.223
Betty, I want you to meet my dad.

08:53.300 --> 08:55.097
Okay. All right, we're in.

08:57.771 --> 08:58.897
What!

09:02.910 --> 09:05.708
I figured the best way to make
a good first impression on Mr. Hartley

09:05.746 --> 09:07.213
was to learn as much about him
as I can.

09:07.248 --> 09:09.182
Did you know he went into outer space?

09:09.216 --> 09:13.016
I wish I was that rich.
I'd like to go into outer space.

09:13.053 --> 09:16.113
Wow, there are, like,
a million interviews with him.

09:16.156 --> 09:18.215
<i>Here's one
in the Dubai Financial Times.</i>

09:18.259 --> 09:22.093
"Hartley made his reputation riding
to the rescue of struggling companies. "

09:22.129 --> 09:24.461
I'd like to rescue struggling companies.

09:24.498 --> 09:27.160
Daniel, we are a struggling company.

09:27.234 --> 09:29.498
Listen. "Among the assets
Hartley considers

09:29.570 --> 09:32.640
"undervalued and ripe for reinvestment
are media companies,

09:32.640 --> 09:35.871
"including newspaper
and magazine publishing. "

09:36.510 --> 09:38.603
- He said that?
- Yeah.

09:39.980 --> 09:43.245
Daniel, what if we got Hartley
to invest in Meade?

09:43.284 --> 09:46.742
- He could be our white knight.
- He could save the company.

09:46.920 --> 09:50.287
No, but Hartley is
notoriously hard to get to.

09:52.559 --> 09:55.050
- Do you really think you can set it up?
- Are you kidding?

09:55.095 --> 09:58.394
Matt would be more than happy to set
up a meeting with you and his father.

09:58.432 --> 10:00.832
- Betty, if you can pull this off...
- I can do it.

10:01.268 --> 10:03.259
- I can't do it.
- It's just a meeting.

10:03.337 --> 10:04.361
I can't.

10:04.438 --> 10:06.269
Daniel only wants a chance
to talk to your dad.

10:06.307 --> 10:08.275
Look, everybody wants
to talk to my father.

10:08.342 --> 10:10.606
Invitations to the White House,
remember?

10:10.644 --> 10:12.874
Everybody in the world always wants
something from him.

10:12.913 --> 10:16.144
No, but, Matt, it's not like that.
This is an opportunity for him.

10:16.183 --> 10:17.707
And it's always an opportunity.

10:17.751 --> 10:20.982
Betty, look, you have to trust me.
It is not a good idea.

10:21.021 --> 10:24.422
- But, Matt...
- No. I'm sorry. The answer is no.

10:53.153 --> 10:55.587
I don't know what to do.
Daniel really needs my help,

10:55.622 --> 10:57.556
but I don't want to do
anything to upset Matt.

10:57.591 --> 10:59.616
Poor Matt.

10:59.660 --> 11:03.619
You don't know how much pressure is
on these rich people. It's incredible.

11:03.664 --> 11:05.359
And what do you know
about rich people?

11:05.399 --> 11:08.994
<i>Excuse me? I've been watching
Dynasty on the Soap channel.</i>

11:09.069 --> 11:10.229
They're not like us.

11:10.304 --> 11:12.204
<i>Listen, I don't know about Dynasty,</i>

11:12.239 --> 11:14.230
but if the choice is between
disappointing your boss

11:14.308 --> 11:17.539
or keeping your rich boyfriend happy,
show me the money.

11:17.578 --> 11:19.910
Yeah, it's like
when Blake has to choose

11:19.947 --> 11:22.245
between his wife Krystle
and her lookalike Rita,

11:22.282 --> 11:24.375
also played by Linda Evans
in a red wig.

11:26.053 --> 11:27.850
Catch up, people.

11:28.155 --> 11:32.091
<i>You know, mi hija, you tried to help out,
and it didn't work.</i>

11:32.126 --> 11:36.062
Daniel will understand.
Just tell him the truth.

11:36.096 --> 11:40.328
<i>You're probably right, papi.
I should just tell him the truth.</i>

11:42.736 --> 11:46.968
Look at little William here. This shot
really brings out that Slater chin.

11:47.007 --> 11:50.306
Honestly, Willie, you haven't had
a Slater chin since 1981.

11:50.344 --> 11:52.972
Well, look at these cheekbones, see?

11:53.881 --> 11:57.317
Well, as much as I live
to tell you what you want to hear,

11:57.351 --> 11:59.216
I don't think babies have cheekbones.

11:59.253 --> 12:01.915
Well, then he must take
after Bradford, I suppose.

12:01.955 --> 12:04.014
Actually, except for
the fish-belly complexion,

12:04.057 --> 12:06.048
I don't see Bradford in there, either.

12:09.963 --> 12:13.831
- What's this all about, Willie?
- Nothing, I guess. It's just...

12:13.901 --> 12:17.837
Well, Miles says the baby looks
a lot like Christina.

12:17.905 --> 12:20.169
Oh, my God, he does.

12:20.974 --> 12:23.704
I mean, does he? Really? I don't see it.

12:23.744 --> 12:25.712
Marc, this is my baby.

12:25.746 --> 12:29.807
I don't care what that overrated
lens-jockey Miles Foster says.

12:29.850 --> 12:32.080
- I know my own child.
- Of course you do.

12:32.119 --> 12:33.484
Why are we even discussing this?

12:33.520 --> 12:35.852
We were both there
when they did the procedure.

12:35.889 --> 12:40.121
It was your egg mixed
with Bradford's swim team.

12:40.160 --> 12:43.186
The baby can't be Christina's.
It's medically impossible.

12:43.230 --> 12:46.961
- Actually, it is medically possible.
- You're joking.

12:47.000 --> 12:49.662
If the surrogate had sexual intercourse
before the implantation,

12:49.736 --> 12:51.465
it's possible she was already pregnant.

12:51.538 --> 12:53.005
In that case,
your egg wouldn't have taken,

12:53.073 --> 12:55.439
and the baby would be
her biological child.

12:57.311 --> 12:59.142
Well, that's all very educational.

13:00.781 --> 13:02.715
Thank you for coming down, Doctor.

13:04.284 --> 13:06.013
- That's it?
- Yes.

13:06.553 --> 13:08.282
Because you said it was urgent.

13:09.556 --> 13:12.855
- I rushed out of surgery to get here.
- Thank you.

13:18.465 --> 13:23.869
Marc, dear God,
William might not be mine.

13:23.904 --> 13:26.668
- I'm so sorry.
- Well, it's... It's unacceptable.

13:26.707 --> 13:28.504
Without little William's share
of the company,

13:28.542 --> 13:30.407
I go back to being a paid employee

13:30.444 --> 13:33.140
with Daniel's girlish fingers
at my throat.

13:33.180 --> 13:37.913
I need you to find out if Christina had
sex right before the procedure,

13:37.951 --> 13:39.919
and do it discreetly.

13:52.199 --> 13:55.066
- Daniel, I need to talk to you.
- And I want to talk to you, too.

13:55.135 --> 13:57.262
All right, guys, thank you, everyone.

13:57.337 --> 13:59.635
Good work. I think it's time to go home
and get some rest.

13:59.673 --> 14:02.073
Have you been here all night?
Why didn't you call me?

14:02.109 --> 14:04.077
Well, I know you're busy with Matt.

14:04.111 --> 14:06.579
We decided to go all-in
on your Hartley idea.

14:06.613 --> 14:07.637
- All-in?
- Yep.

14:07.681 --> 14:09.911
I called in marketing,
ad sales, the art department...

14:09.950 --> 14:13.181
And we put together such a kick-ass
proposal for my meeting with Hartley.

14:13.220 --> 14:15.279
Daniel, before you start kicking ass...

14:15.322 --> 14:20.089
Just wait till you see what we came up
with. We are gonna blow him away.

14:20.594 --> 14:23.859
<i>For over 100 years,
Meade Publications has helped</i>

14:23.897 --> 14:28.857
<i>to educate, inform, and entertain
generations of Americans.</i>

14:28.936 --> 14:32.838
<i>Now, leading this bold charge
into the next millennium</i>

14:32.873 --> 14:36.934
<i>is a true visionary,
businessman, humanitarian,</i>

14:36.977 --> 14:40.640
<i>and world-class athlete, Daniel Meade.</i>

14:41.915 --> 14:45.146
- Athlete?
- Yeah, I was on the crew team, JV.

14:45.185 --> 14:47.517
Besides, if Hartley's gonna put money
into Meade, the company,

14:47.554 --> 14:50.717
he's got to have confidence
in Meade, the man.

14:51.258 --> 14:52.350
Did you notice I got that guy

14:52.392 --> 14:54.155
who did the voice for Hartley's
to do mine?

14:54.194 --> 14:56.924
- Daniel, I...
- I mean, it's still a work in progress.

14:56.964 --> 14:59.194
We're gonna Photoshop the margarita
out of my hand,

14:59.266 --> 15:02.429
maybe put in, like, an orphaned baby.

15:02.469 --> 15:04.403
Betty, I gotta tell you,
this is the first time in months

15:04.438 --> 15:07.236
I feel like we actually have a chance.

15:08.175 --> 15:10.166
So, what do you think?

15:12.079 --> 15:13.273
He's gonna love it.

15:14.681 --> 15:17.309
You're gonna knock his socks off
in that meeting.

15:17.351 --> 15:20.445
You didn't really say
"knock his socks off," did you?

15:20.487 --> 15:23.422
It just came out. What am I gonna do?

15:23.457 --> 15:26.654
Daniel thinks that this meeting with
Hartley could help save the company,

15:26.693 --> 15:28.558
and I have to tell him
it's not even going to happen.

15:28.595 --> 15:31.758
Well, the man is a "true visionary,"
so he may already know.

15:31.999 --> 15:34.399
There he is.

15:34.468 --> 15:38.199
There's the little product of
an unholy deal with the devil.

15:38.271 --> 15:40.330
Yes, you are.

15:40.407 --> 15:42.341
- You're so good with him.
- Who knew?

15:42.376 --> 15:45.971
I thought my only maternal instinct
was nursing a bottle of whiskey.

15:46.013 --> 15:47.605
Stuart's coming by in a little while,

15:47.648 --> 15:49.809
and we're gonna go
for a walk in the park.

15:49.850 --> 15:53.251
- How is Stuart?
- Better, actually.

15:53.286 --> 15:55.083
At first we thought
the treatment wasn't working,

15:55.122 --> 15:57.056
but he seems to be improving.

15:57.090 --> 15:59.490
And you should see him
with this little ankle-biter,

15:59.526 --> 16:02.654
all cooing and making faces.

