And seeing those kids' smiling faces

34:40.114 --> 34:43.743
would sure put me in the mood
to talk business.

34:54.795 --> 34:57.765
I got it! I got the egg!

34:59.033 --> 35:01.866
<i>Congratulations. Now, why don't you
step up here, young lady?</i>

35:01.903 --> 35:05.862
<i>- Okay, excuse me, excuse me.
- Excuse me, kids. Here we go.</i>

35:05.940 --> 35:08.465
<i>Now, since you found
the Fabergé egg,</i>

35:08.543 --> 35:11.205
<i>valued at more than
half a million dollars...</i>

35:11.245 --> 35:12.803
Oh, my God!

35:12.847 --> 35:15.441
<i>...it will now be auctioned off,
and the proceeds donated</i>

35:15.483 --> 35:18.111
<i>to New York Children's Hospital
in your name.</i>

35:21.022 --> 35:22.546
But I... I found it.

35:22.590 --> 35:26.287
- I found the egg, sir. This isn't fair.
- All right, sweetheart. Time to go.

35:27.528 --> 35:29.519
<i>Isn't she wonderful?</i>

35:30.164 --> 35:32.064
No. I found the egg.

35:43.444 --> 35:45.435
Are we finished?
Do you hate me, Matt?

35:45.513 --> 35:47.276
Because I hate me right now, and...

35:47.315 --> 35:51.115
No. No, no, I could
never hate you. Never.

35:52.186 --> 35:54.950
And you were right.
People's jobs are at stake.

35:54.989 --> 35:56.354
I mean, your friends are getting fired

35:56.390 --> 35:58.654
because I have
some crazy rich-boy daddy issues.

35:58.693 --> 35:59.717
That's messed up.

35:59.760 --> 36:03.218
No, Matt, I still should not have
gone behind your back.

36:03.264 --> 36:05.892
True, you owe me for that one.

36:05.933 --> 36:08.595
I may have to cancel
Submarine Thursdays.

36:09.837 --> 36:13.432
Betty, I just hope you don't regret
hooking Daniel up with my father.

36:13.507 --> 36:15.031
Why would I?

36:15.109 --> 36:18.738
My dad can be a great guy, but you do
not want to go into business with him.

36:18.779 --> 36:22.772
He needs to control everything.
I've spent my entire life

36:22.817 --> 36:25.945
trying to keep him as far away
from my career as possible.

36:25.987 --> 36:29.684
That's why I didn't want him investing
in Meade, working in publishing.

36:29.724 --> 36:32.420
I mean, I finally found something
that was mine.

36:32.460 --> 36:35.088
But, Matt, you don't even work
at Meade.

36:35.129 --> 36:39.259
But you do. Betty, you don't know
where this could lead.

36:39.800 --> 36:42.166
Come on, it can't be that bad.

36:42.470 --> 36:44.131
It's Floppy!

36:44.572 --> 36:46.904
Floppy!

36:48.843 --> 36:50.504
Hi, Floppy!
Hi, Floppy!

36:55.116 --> 36:56.743
Is that Daniel?

36:57.451 --> 36:59.112
I want an egg.

37:00.488 --> 37:02.422
It's Daniel Meade.

37:03.891 --> 37:06.291
You thought my mom was
the tough one?

37:06.327 --> 37:08.158
My mom is like an Easter egg,

37:08.195 --> 37:11.528
hard on the outside,
but soft and gooey on the inside.

37:11.565 --> 37:15.092
Dad's more like Satan.

38:08.889 --> 38:13.952
Daniel, I am so sorry.
I had no idea this would happen.

38:14.328 --> 38:16.660
- It's okay.
- No, it's not okay.

38:16.697 --> 38:18.961
Matt tried to warn me,
and I wouldn't listen,

38:19.000 --> 38:21.730
- and his father humiliated you.
- Betty.

38:24.071 --> 38:25.538
We did it.

38:26.741 --> 38:28.106
What?

38:28.142 --> 38:32.545
I just spent 10 minutes with Hartley,
running the numbers. He's in.

38:33.547 --> 38:38.211
He's actually delaying his trip to Siberia
so we can make a full proposal.

38:38.986 --> 38:42.854
He said he looks forward to being
in the publishing business.

38:43.391 --> 38:45.552
Oh, my God! That's amazing.

38:47.094 --> 38:49.756
Well, but what about all of this?

38:50.297 --> 38:53.164
It's just to prove what a big man he is.

38:53.634 --> 38:56.330
- So, you knew what he was doing?
- Yeah, of course I did.

38:56.404 --> 38:59.498
I've been dealing with ego-driven
bastards like him my whole life.

39:00.307 --> 39:02.832
No, I've made a fool of myself
enough times for no reason.

39:02.877 --> 39:05.641
I can do it once to save our company.

39:06.714 --> 39:10.172
Daniel, I'm so proud of you.

39:13.254 --> 39:14.744
What's that?

39:15.856 --> 39:19.792
It's just my cottontail.
I was using it to stop the bleeding.

39:20.928 --> 39:23.328
Those kids were vicious, huh?

39:37.244 --> 39:39.371
Here they are,
the lab results.

39:39.880 --> 39:42.440
You haven't opened it?
- No, I...

39:43.217 --> 39:46.277
I didn't have the nerve.
You... You open it.

39:55.896 --> 40:00.458
It's yours. The baby's yours.

40:02.837 --> 40:04.065
Thank God.

40:04.138 --> 40:06.868
I was just... I was so sure.

40:07.608 --> 40:12.875
Well, now that that is settled,
I will be making other arrangements

40:12.913 --> 40:14.938
- for William's care.
- What do you mean?

40:14.982 --> 40:17.917
I will no longer be needing
your services as nanny.

40:17.952 --> 40:19.146
Given the circumstances,

40:19.186 --> 40:22.644
I think it's best that
you stay away from my child.

40:23.757 --> 40:25.247
Permanently.

40:32.266 --> 40:36.760
<i>There's a light that just won't go out</i>

40:36.837 --> 40:40.273
<i>No matter what they try to do</i>

40:40.307 --> 40:41.706
Morning.

40:42.643 --> 40:47.103
<i>'Cause you can't pull out the circuits</i>

40:47.148 --> 40:49.946
<i>Remove the bulb</i>

40:49.984 --> 40:51.246
Messages.

40:51.285 --> 40:52.718
<i>Or blow the fuse</i>

40:53.187 --> 40:58.090
<i>And it just might be the brightest star</i>

40:58.325 --> 41:02.091
<i>Discovered yet by man</i>

41:03.430 --> 41:07.696
<i>But it might as well be a pin hole</i>

41:07.735 --> 41:14.241
<i>From where we stand</i>

41:14.241 --> 41:18.041
<i>So don't feel bad</i>

41:19.647 --> 41:23.811
<i>Don't look so sad</i>

41:24.685 --> 41:27.950
<i>We're much more than that</i>

41:27.988 --> 41:31.947
<i>But for now it's a deathtrap</i>

41:34.094 --> 41:35.857
A carrot basket.

41:38.265 --> 41:41.029
At least Hartley
has a sense of humor.

41:44.605 --> 41:47.301
<i>It's a deathtrap</i>

41:48.876 --> 41:52.505
<i>And it's gonna get worse</i>

